[It is unclear when the victim first developed symptoms but his presentation is consistent with an influenza event culminating in progressive influenza pneumonia or a secondary bacterial pneumonia and death. Other respiratory viral processes can produce a similar outcome but, if the contacts do indeed have the same infectious agent, influenza virus would be at the top of the differential diagnosis list. As recognized in the 2009 pandemic, the young adult cohort (similar to what occurred in the Great Pandemic of 1918-1919) had a mortality rate out of proportion to what occurs in seasonal influenza. ProMED-mail would appreciate more information regarding this cluster of cases in northern Lebanon. - Mod.LL

Maps of Lebanon can be seen at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2341995,14906 and http://m.cdn.blog.hu/ka/katpol/image/lebanon%20districts.jpg. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
